title: TidGi Feature Handbook/Open Workspace in New Window
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

TidGi lets you open the same workspace in a separate new window. Content in both windows is kept in sync in real time via SSE.

!! Opening a New Window

Right-click the workspace icon in the sidebar and choose "Open in New Window". The workspace opens in an independent window.

!! Real-Time Cross-Window Sync

* When you edit a tiddler in any window (after saving), the other window automatically receives the update and refreshes that tiddler
* Sync is bidirectional: changes in the main window push to the new window, and changes in the new window push back to the main window
* Uses SSE (Server-Sent Events) for push delivery with minimal latency

!! Use Cases

* Browse reference material in one window while writing notes in another
* Multi-monitor setup: show different tiddlers from the same workspace on separate screens
* Use the new window as a "read-only display" while editing in the main window

!! Notes

* Both windows share the same backend process, so the extra memory overhead is minimal
* Closing the main window does not close the new window (they are independent)
